	quest.0DCC71420C57E089.quest_desc: [
		"It's said that once in every Cactoid's life, he enters a strange mood and seeks out rare organic materials. In this temporary state, the Cactoid's genetically-engineered instincts let it fuse biology with metal to forge a unique living tool, a phenomenon known as \"biosmithing\"."
		"Your instincts cry out - this crossbow could be something more, if only you had the right parts! You sense the need for tentacles, yes... giant orange tentacles, from a leviathan of the deep sea! But even if such a beast existed in this world, you might never find it..."
		"Plan B: slaughter enough fish, rip open their guts, and surely you'd find a few decent tentacles in their stomachs."
	]
	quest.0DCC71420C57E089.title: "Fish Fear Me"
